properties.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued January 9 at 2:33PM PST until January 10 at 3:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Minor coastal flooding expected.

* WHERE...North Coast and Central Coast.

* WHEN...From 9 AM to 3 PM PST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Flooding of lots, parks, and roads with only
isolated road closures expected.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The combination of high astronomical tide,
strong onshore winds and low pressure may result in minor tidal
overflow, especially in the town of Aberdeen. High tide at
Aberdeen is around 11:36 AM PST at 11.4 feet. The tidal anomaly
is 1 to 1.5 feet. High water levels in the Chehalis River will
contribute to minor flooding in Aberdeen.
properties.instruction:
A Coastal Flood Advisory indicates that onshore winds and tides
will combine to generate flooding of low areas along the shore.

If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be
closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of
unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone
property.

NWSheadline: COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 9 AM TO 3 PM PST FRIDAY
